    "description": "Create a MIME-compliant header that can contain strings in different character sets. Optional s is the initial header value. If None (the default), the initial header value is not set. You can later append to the header with append() method calls. s may be an instance of bytes or str, but see the append() documentation for semantics. Optional charset serves two purposes: it has the same meaning as the charset argument to the append() method. It also sets the default character set for all subs...",
